(54, 'Wireless Network Security for Users', 'Steve F. Russell', 'Network secitrih technology generally concentrates on\nprotection of the network infrastri~ture and, by\nitnplication, the protection of the itser. While this is true\nfor the larger public network, the local network\nenvironment of the user is veni vulnerable to denial-of-\nservice, tiinti-in-the-niiddle, and other attacks that can\nbe devastciting. In this paper, we examine the issues of\nrcireless secitrih from the perspective of the user and the\nlocal network. We will look at airlink attacks by\nspecialized tmnstnitters and intercept receivers. Examples\nnfll be taken f r o m the technologies used in IS-95 CDMA\ncelliilar radiotelephone ond IEEE 802.I I wireless LANs', 'a:52:{i:1;s:1:"*";i:4;s:6:"jurnal";i:8;s:1:"-";i:9;s:5:"judul";i:10;d:0.29999999999999999;i:11;s:2:"*j";i:12;s:6:"juduls";i:13;s:2:"-j";i:14;d:0.29999999999999999;i:15;s:4:"user";i:16;s:2:"-j";i:17;d:0.29999999999999999;i:18;s:5:"secur";i:19;s:2:"-j";i:20;d:0.29999999999999999;i:21;s:7:"network";i:22;s:1:"#";i:23;s:1:"-";i:24;s:7:"keyword";i:25;d:0.40000000000000002;i:26;s:2:"*k";i:27;s:8:"keywords";i:28;s:2:"-k";i:29;d:0.29999999999999999;i:30;s:8:"wireless";i:31;s:2:"-k";i:32;d:0.29999999999999999;i:33;s:7:"network";i:34;s:2:"-k";i:35;d:0.20000000000000001;i:36;s:4:"user";i:37;s:1:"#";i:38;s:1:"-";i:39;s:7:"penulis";i:40;d:0.20000000000000001;i:41;s:2:"*p";i:42;s:8:"penuliss";i:43;s:2:"-p";i:44;d:0.29999999999999999;i:45;s:7:"russell";i:46;s:2:"-p";i:47;d:0.29999999999999999;i:48;s:1:"f";i:49;s:2:"-p";i:50;d:0.29999999999999999;i:51;s:5:"steve";i:52;s:1:"#";i:53;s:1:"-";i:54;s:5:"tahun";i:55;d:0.10000000000000001;i:56;s:4:"2001";i:57;s:1:"#";}', 'a:3:{i:0;a:2:{s:4:"kata";s:4:"user";s:5:"bobot";d:0.29999999999999999;}i:1;a:2:{s:4:"kata";s:5:"secur";s:5:"bobot";d:0.29999999999999999;}i:2;a:2:{s:4:"kata";s:7:"network";s:5:"bobot";d:0.29999999999999999;}}', 'a:3:{i:0;a:2:{s:4:"kata";s:8:"wireless";s:5:"bobot";d:0.29999999999999999;}i